In the information age, the barriers [to entry into programming] just aren't
there. The barriers are self imposed. If you want to set off and go develop
some grand new thing, you don't need millions of dollars of capitalization. You
need enough pizza and Diet Coke to stick in your refrigerator, a cheap PC to
work on, and the dedication to go through with it. We slept on floors.
We waded across rivers.

- John Carmack
  Masters of Doom: How Two Guys Created an Empire
  and Transformed Pop Culture
