Programming is really just the mundane aspect of expressing a solution
to a problem. There are talents that are specifically related to actually
coding, but the real issue is being able to grasp problems and devise solutions
that are detailed enough to actually be coded.

- John Carmack
  Slashdot interview
  October 15, 1999
