%
The reason is not to glorify "bit chasing"; a more fundamental issue is at
stake here: Numerical subroutines should deliver results that satisfy simple,
useful mathematical laws whenever possible. [...] Without any underlying
symmetry properties, the job of proving interesting results becomes
extremely unpleasant. The enjoyment of one's tools is an essential ingredient
of successful work.

- Donald Knuth
  The Art Of Computer Programming
  Vol. II, Seminumerical Algorithms
